org.seedstack.audit

Annotation Type Audited


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Audited
    An annotation used to automatically audit a method. A message before the execution of the method can be defined. A message at the end of the execution must be defined. If an exception occurs in the method, a message can also be defined. Each message can be an EL (Expression language) which will be evaluated with the context of the method (arguments, return, exception...)
    Author:
    yves.dautremay@mpsa.com
